Medieval philosophers used to hold the sensible belief that it was more perfect to exist than not to exist , and that to exist as a matter of necessity was most perfect of all .
Now , <COREF ID="10" TYPE="IDENT">only God</COREF> <COREF ID="9" TYPE="IDENT">exists</COREF> as a matter of absolute necessity ; <COREF ID="9" TYPE="IDENT">it</COREF> is built into <COREF ID="10" TYPE="IDENT">His</COREF> nature .
