<COREF ID="16" TYPE="IDENT">One</COREF> was so fantastic in appearance , <COREF ID="16" TYPE="IDENT">it</COREF> was dubbed Hallucigenia .
Would that <COREF ID="7" TYPE="IDENT">Mr. Gould 's</COREF> minute descriptions of <COREF ID="1" TYPE="IDENT">these creatures</COREF> was always so colorful .
A good deal of <COREF ID="17" TYPE="IDENT">the book</COREF> is boring , particularly the endless allusions to high and pop culture and the frequent jokes festooning the text .
These turns do not provide sufficient relief from sentences like , `` Most modern chelicerates have six uniramous appendages on the prosoma . ''
